abstract: Teachers from around the country suggest how, and why, to help students make sense of this historic moment.

lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, President Trump became the third president in United States history to be impeached by the House of Representatives.

headline_main: Teaching Impeachment: 7 Ideas From Our Readers

abstract: The president traveled to Michigan, a vital electoral state, to deliver his response after he became the third president to be impeached by the House.
snippet: The president traveled to Michigan, a vital electoral state, to deliver his response after he became the third president to be impeached by the House.
lead_paragraph: BATTLE CREEK, Mich. — President Trump angrily responded to the impeachment he had long been dreading on Wednesday, lashing out at his Democratic accusers in a rambling two-hour speech and calling for their defeat in November.

abstract: A key U.S. House committee on Wednesday released a draft of a bipartisan consumer privacy bill, which would set nationwide rules for handling of personal information online and draw new safeguards around how companies can collect and use such data.
snippet: A key U.S. House committee on Wednesday released a draft of a bipartisan consumer privacy bill, which would set nationwide rules for handling of personal information online and draw new safeguards around how companies can collect and use such data...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A key U.S. House committee on Wednesday released a draft of a bipartisan consumer privacy bill, which would set nationwide rules for handling of personal information online and draw new safeguards around how companies can collect and use such data.
headline_main: Latest Draft of U.S. Federal Privacy Bill Sidesteps Key Sticking Points
headline_print_headline: Latest Draft of U.S. Federal Privacy Bill Sidesteps Key Sticking Points

abstract: Britain urged China on Thursday to open dialogue with Hong Kong protesters and respect the commitments it made 35 years ago in the Sino-British Joint Declaration.
snippet: Britain urged China on Thursday to open dialogue with Hong Kong protesters and respect the commitments it made 35 years ago in the Sino-British Joint Declaration.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain urged China on Thursday to open dialogue with Hong Kong protesters and respect the commitments it made 35 years ago in the Sino-British Joint Declaration.
headline_main: UK Urges China to Open Dialogue With Hong Kong on 1984 Declaration Anniversary
headline_print_headline: UK Urges China to Open Dialogue With Hong Kong on 1984 Declaration Anniversary

abstract: The candidates must know the quirks of California’s vast political geography.
snippet: The candidates must know the quirks of California’s vast political geography.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Welcome, Democrats and debate spinners, to the city with a Mexican-American-Jewish-Italian Rhodes Scholar mayor, who is not running for president, in the state with an Irish Catholic governor who surely is, just not this time.

abstract: Illinois Gov. J.B. Pritzker on Wednesday consolidated pension programs for most of the state's police officers and firefighters outside the Chicago area, a move he said would expand the funds by up to $2.5 billion over five years while cutting administrative costs for local governments.
snippet: Illinois Gov. J.B. Pritzker on Wednesday consolidated pension programs for most of the state's police officers and firefighters outside the Chicago area, a move he said would expand the funds by up to $2.5 billion over five years while cutting adm...
lead_paragraph: SPRINGFIELD, Ill. — Illinois Gov. J.B. Pritzker on Wednesday consolidated pension programs for most of the state's police officers and firefighters outside the Chicago area, a move he said would expand the funds by up to $2.5 billion over five years while cutting administrative costs for local governments.
headline_main: Illinois Governor Merges Pension Funds in Cost-Cutting Move
headline_print_headline: Illinois Governor Merges Pension Funds in Cost-Cutting Move

abstract: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson will set out his government's plans on Thursday, fleshing out how he will honor his election-winning pledges to get Brexit done quickly and boost funding for the state health service.
snippet: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson will set out his government's plans on Thursday, fleshing out how he will honor his election-winning pledges to get Brexit done quickly and boost funding for the state health service.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British Prime Minister Boris Johnson will set out his government's plans on Thursday, fleshing out how he will honor his election-winning pledges to get Brexit done quickly and boost funding for the state health service.
headline_main: Brexit and Health, Britain's Johnson Sets Out Priorities in Queen's Speech
headline_print_headline: Brexit and Health, Britain's Johnson Sets Out Priorities in Queen's Speech

abstract: The United Nations General Assembly on Wednesday condemned "the long-standing and ongoing systematic, widespread and gross violations of human rights in and by" North Korea in an annual resolution that Pyongyang's U.N. envoy rejected.
snippet: The United Nations General Assembly on Wednesday condemned "the long-standing and ongoing systematic, widespread and gross violations of human rights in and by" North Korea in an annual resolution that Pyongyang's U.N. envoy rejected.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The United Nations General Assembly on Wednesday condemned "the long-standing and ongoing systematic, widespread and gross violations of human rights in and by" North Korea in an annual resolution that Pyongyang's U.N. envoy rejected.
headline_main: U.N. Condemns North Korea Rights Abuses, Pyongyang Rejects Resolution
headline_print_headline: U.N. Condemns North Korea Rights Abuses, Pyongyang Rejects Resolution
